readables/man2/journal_ingleby
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "1"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		"Finally everyone is off  to bed! I hope that cook didn't poison everyone, he didn't seem too pleased about having to work all weekend.  It clearly states in his contract he will occasionally be expected to work extra hours."
		""
		"Either way he's been rather disagreeable the last few weeks and I'm starting to  have my suspicions about him. Some of our silverware has gone missing so I'm putting everything in the"
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		"safe from now on.  I will speak to Twistleton about getting him replaced in the morning..."
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/books/book_calig_camberic.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
}


readables/man2/journal_twistleton
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "3"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		"2nd August, 1634"
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"Ever since the Crown imposed those taxes on exports, I've been making a fortune. There is no shortage of grain or livestock in this country and overseas buyers are willing to pay over the odds for it.  Instead of being fleeced by the taxman,  local merchants are coming to me to broker the "
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		"sale of their wares."
		""
		"I've decided to invest my profits in the local property market.  First I will renovate my current house, and then I will convert the houses across the street into flats.  I shall call them 'Highclere House'!"
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
	{
		"24 September, 1634"
	}
	"page2_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"Some unexpected good luck.  While renovating one of the houses across the road, one of the workers uncovered an old mining tunnel.  After some initial exploration, it appears that it passes directly underneath The Hare in the Snare Inn, where I have publically (and reluctantly) been meeting with foreign merchants."
	}
	"page2_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_right_body"	:
	{
		"If we can ensure this tunnel is safe, perhaps we can arrange for a more clandestine operation."
		""
		"The innkeeper, Bennet, is fond of coin and won't be an obstacle."
	}
	"page3_left_title"	:
	{
		"16th October, 1634"
	}
	"page3_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"It's all falling into place now.  I've hired staff to look after my little housing development and one of them, Hales, is an ex-City Watch officer.  She got into a little bit of trouble and therefore has ended up in the 'private sector'.  She seems competent enough, although a bit short-tempered."
	}
	"page3_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page3_right_body"	:
	{
		"Either way, she is perfect for handling the dirty work for me, as I need to start keeping a lower profile."
		""
		"The public needs to believe I earn my fortune from property, not smuggling!"
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/books/book_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
	"gui_page2"	: "guis/readables/books/book_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
	"gui_page3"	: "guis/readables/books/book_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
}


readables/man2/note_twistleton_from_hales
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "2"
	"page1_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"Sir,"
		""
		"I'm afraid there's been an... incident. "
		""
		"Bennet the innkeeper informed me that someone by the name of Jacobs was making a lot of inquiries about goings -on at the inn, and they weren't about 'commercial opportunities'."
		""
		"As I was preparing to investigate, I caught the very same fellow snooping around Highclere House.  He was easily "
	}
	"page2_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_body"	:
	{
		""
		"disarmed,but clammed up when questioned."
		""
		"I took him down into the tunnel and handed him over to the Daltons for further interrogation, but unfortunately they got a bit carried away."
		""
		"Rest assured, this will be dealt with and you shall not hear anymore about it again."
		""
		"Hales"
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/sheets/sheet_paper_hand_nancy.gui"
	"gui_page2"	: "guis/readables/sheets/sheet_paper_hand_nancy.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
}


readables/man2/note_thugs_from_hales
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "1"
	"page1_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_body"	:
	{
		"You two morons need to clean up your mess in the next room.  I even brought you some shovels."
		""
		"When you finish that, come and see me for your wages and then I never want to see either of you again.  When you were hired I explained, in excruciating detail, how we prefer to work here.  In retrospect, perhaps I used too many words."
		""
		"Hales"
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/sheets/sheet_paper_hand_nancy.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
}


readables/man2/journal_jacobs
{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "2"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		"03/02"
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"...arrived at the inn tonight.  Not a bad place really, just needs a bit of a work.  Certainly not the dive I was expecting."
		""
		"The innkeeper got a bit funny though when I asked how business was going."
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		"05/02"
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		""
		""
		"According to the locals, half this town is owned by 'Lord' Twistleton, although the provenance of that title is suspect.  He apparently showed up about a year ago and started buying up property, starting with his house across the street, which I hear is pretty fancy."
	}
	"page2_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_left_body"	:
	{
		"He's also acquired and renovated all of Morden Place, calling it 'Highclere House' and letting it out as flats to wealthier business-types who have more money than sense."
		""
		"Either way I'm going to see what else I can turn up.  Between the twitchy inkeeper and this dodgy Twistleton character "
	}
	"page2_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page2_right_body"	:
	{
		"something is going on, and perhaps there is more to be had here than pilfering a few trinkets from a rich noble."
		""
		"I'll start by asking around in the tavern and then maybe having a nose around this Highclere House place..."
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/books/book_hand_ellianerelle.gui"
	"gui_page2"	: "guis/readables/books/book_hand_ellianerelle.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
}


