{
	precache
	"num_pages"	: "1"
	"page1_left_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_left_body"	:
	{
		"Well I suppose this 'flat' isn't a terrible place to live, although it's not the proper house that befits an Ingleby.  Gerald explained that living closer to the centre of town is what 'men of influence' do these days.  He has done well since his time in the Guards."
		""
		"I've never heard of this Lord Twistleton chap, the landlord.  I'll have to ask around about him when we return home.  "
	}
	"page1_right_title"	:
	{
		""
	}
	"page1_right_body"	:
	{
		"At least he lives close by.  In fact, I can see someone fooling around in his attic across the street."
		""
		"What on earth did that fool of a cook serve us this evening?  I've spent half the night visiting the toilet..."
	}
	"gui_page1"	: "guis/readables/books/book_calig_mac_humaine.gui"
	"snd_page_turn"	: "readable_page_turn"
